# IE4228 Assignment 1 — Grading Rubric

> **Traditional Face Detection and Recognition System (PCA / LDA)**
>
> Total: **100 points** &nbsp;|&nbsp; Live Demo: Week 12/13 &nbsp;|&nbsp; Report deadline: before lab assessment week

---

## Scoring Guide

| Grade | Range | Description |
|-------|-------|-------------|
| A+ / A | 85–100 | Exceeds expectations; thorough understanding of PCA/LDA theory, rigorous evaluation |
| A− / B+ | 75–84 | Meets all requirements with solid technical depth |
| B / B− | 60–74 | Meets core requirements with minor gaps |
| C+ / C | 50–59 | Minimal viable submission; significant gaps |
| D / F | 0–49 | Incomplete or non-functional |

---

## 1. Face Detection (Viola-Jones) — 15 pts

| Criterion | Excellent (13–15) | Good (10–12) | Adequate (7–9) | Poor (0–6) |
|-----------|-------------------|--------------|-----------------|------------|
| **Haar Cascade usage & understanding** | Uses OpenCV Haar Cascade with clear explanation of Viola-Jones algorithm (integral images, AdaBoost, cascade stages). Tunes `scaleFactor`, `minNeighbors`, `minSize` with justification. | Uses Haar Cascade correctly; briefly explains the algorithm and default parameters. | Uses Haar Cascade as a black box with no parameter tuning or explanation. | No face detection or manual cropping only. |
| **Detection accuracy** | Tight bounding boxes on all team members under varying lighting and distance; handles profile faces via multiple cascades. | Bounding boxes present and mostly accurate; occasional misses on angled faces. | Bounding boxes present but noticeably inaccurate or miss small faces. | Bounding boxes missing or consistently wrong. |
| **Robustness & fallback** | Graceful fallback when no face detected (e.g. use whole image); handles multi-scale detection well. | Minor issues with edge cases; mostly functional. | Crashes or produces errors when no face detected. | Detection non-functional. |

---

## 2. Face Recognition (PCA / LDA) — 20 pts

| Criterion | Excellent (17–20) | Good (13–16) | Adequate (9–12) | Poor (0–8) |
|-----------|-------------------|--------------|-----------------|------------|
| **Eigenfaces / Fisherfaces understanding** | Demonstrates deep understanding of PCA (covariance, eigenvectors, projection) and LDA (between-class vs within-class scatter). Explains Small Sample Size (SSS) problem and PCA→LDA cascade solution. | Explains PCA and LDA concepts correctly; mentions SSS problem. | Uses PCA or LDA but with minimal explanation. | No dimensionality reduction; raw pixel matching or no recognition. |
| **Component selection & variance analysis** | Reports PCA explained variance ratios; justifies `n_components` choice with cumulative variance plot. Reports LDA component count relative to number of classes. | Reports component counts; some variance analysis. | Arbitrary component selection with no analysis. | No component selection discussion. |
| **Training / testing metrics & loss** | Reports train/test accuracy, reconstruction error (PCA MSE), confusion matrix, per-class precision/recall. Uses train/test split (e.g. 80/20). Discusses SED threshold selection. | Reports accuracy and basic metrics; some train/test separation. | Reports only pass/fail observations; no formal metrics. | No metrics or evaluation of any kind. |
| **Unknown handling (SED threshold)** | Implements calibrated SED threshold with justification; demonstrates low false-positive rate for unseen faces. | Has threshold-based unknown signal; tested with ≥2 unknown subjects. | "Unknown" label exists but threshold is arbitrary or untested. | No unknown detection. |

