## 3. Pre-processing Pipeline — 10 pts

| Criterion | Excellent (9–10) | Good (7–8) | Adequate (5–6) | Poor (0–4) |
|-----------|------------------|------------|-----------------|------------|
| **Normalisation techniques** | Applies greyscale conversion, histogram equalisation (or CLAHE), and optional gamma correction with clear explanation of why each step improves recognition. | Applies greyscale + histogram equalisation; brief justification. | Only greyscale conversion; no illumination normalisation. | No pre-processing. |
| **Spatial standardisation** | All faces resized to consistent dimensions (e.g. 100×100); alignment or rotation correction attempted. | Consistent resize applied; no alignment. | Inconsistent sizing across gallery and test images. | No spatial normalisation. |

---

## 4. Database & Data Engineering — 10 pts

| Criterion | Excellent (9–10) | Good (7–8) | Adequate (5–6) | Poor (0–4) |
|-----------|------------------|------------|-----------------|------------|
| **Gallery completeness** | ≥ 10 images per person for **all** team members + ≥ 2 additional individuals; varied poses, lighting, and expressions. Modular gallery design allowing easy swap of identities. | ≥ 10 images per person for all team members; limited variation. | < 10 images for some members; minimal diversity. | Gallery incomplete or poorly organized. |
| **Dataset & pipeline** | Uses LFW (or equivalent) for prototyping with scripted download; gallery folder structure is modular (add/remove identities easily); pre-processing pipeline is scripted and reproducible. | Uses a standard dataset; partially scripted pipeline. | Manual or ad-hoc data collection only. | No organised dataset. |

