## 5. Live Demonstration & GUI — 20 pts

| Criterion | Excellent (17–20) | Good (13–16) | Adequate (9–12) | Poor (0–8) |
|-----------|-------------------|--------------|-----------------|------------|
| **Functional demo** | All team members detected and correctly recognized in real-time; unknown faces correctly rejected; smooth, uninterrupted operation. | Most members recognized; ≤ 1 incorrect identification during demo; minor hiccups. | ≥ 50% recognition rate; some crashes or freezes. | Demo non-functional or requires restart. |
| **GUI quality** | Clean, labeled bounding boxes with name overlay; distance/confidence display; professional layout (Tkinter/OpenCV GUI). | Bounding boxes with name labels; basic but functional UI. | Minimal UI; raw OpenCV window with text. | No GUI or command-line only. |
| **Robustness** | Handles multiple simultaneous faces, varying distances, and lighting changes gracefully. | Handles 2–3 faces; some sensitivity to conditions. | Single-face only or very fragile. | Fails under any variation. |

