## 6. Technical Report — 15 pts

| Criterion | Excellent (13–15) | Good (10–12) | Adequate (7–9) | Poor (0–6) |
|-----------|-------------------|--------------|-----------------|------------|
| **Architecture description** | Clear pipeline diagram (detection → pre-processing → PCA → LDA → SED matching); explains each stage with mathematical formulation; cites relevant papers. | Describes pipeline with some detail; references present. | High-level description only; few or no references. | No architecture description. |
| **Performance analysis** | Reports quantitative metrics (accuracy, reconstruction error, variance explained, confusion matrix, train/test split results); compares PCA-only vs PCA+LDA; discusses threshold tuning. | Reports accuracy and some metrics; limited analysis. | Reports only pass/fail observations. | No metrics. |
| **Individual contributions** | Clearly delineated per-member contributions; signed by all members. | Contributions listed but vaguely described. | Contributions section present but incomplete. | Missing contributions or signatures. |
| **Writing quality** | Well-structured, professional, free of major errors. | Readable with minor issues. | Disorganized or hard to follow. | Incomprehensible or largely copy-pasted. |

