> [!TIP]
> **Bonus opportunities (up to +5 extra credit):**
> - Training a custom PCA/LDA model on a larger dataset (e.g. LFW full) with measurable improvement
> - Implementing alternative classifiers (SVM, k-NN) alongside SED with comparative benchmarks
> - Multi-face tracking across frames (e.g. simple centroid tracker)
> - Comprehensive ablation study (PCA-only vs LDA-only vs PCA+LDA)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The rubric values **demonstrated understanding** over mere tool usage. Using sklearn's PCA/LDA is acceptable, but the team must be able to explain *why* it works (eigenvalue decomposition, scatter matrices, projection geometry) and *how* parameter choices affect performance during the oral interview.
